article.headline: Stephen F. Austin 91, Houston Baptist 66
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas (AP) -- Antuane Miller scored a game-high 24 points to lead Stephen F. Austin to a 91-66 victory over Houston Baptist on Tuesday night. Josh Alexander had 14 points and made all four of his 3-point attempts. Anthony Paez added 13 points and six rebounds for Stephen F. Austin (3-1). Marcus Clark had a game-high nine assists. Ben McCain led Houston Baptist (4-1) with 16 points and had a game-high eight rebounds. Dwight Jones had 13 points and Chad Barnes added 11. Barnes and McCain combined to hit the team's only two 3-pointers of the game. Stephen F. Austin shot 50 percent from the field, and Houston Baptist shot 45 percent. Stephen F. Austin led 54-42 at halftime.
